  <summary date="2021-03-03T21:45:21Z" status="Introduced in House">This resolution encourages the recognition of the collective history and achievements of people of African descent and reaffirms the importance of their equal participation in all aspects of political, economic, social, and cultural life.

The resolution also recognizes that many Black Europeans have experienced injustices in the public and private sector and welcomes European efforts to promote racial equality and combat discrimination.

Further, the resolution urges the Department of State and the U.S. Agency for International Development to support efforts to promote equality.</summary>
